Trading Bot Setup Instructions
============================

This document provides instructions for setting up the trading bot on a Linux system.

Prerequisites
------------
- Linux operating system
- Systemd service manager
- Sudo privileges
- Rust toolchain (for building the bot)

Installation Steps
----------------
1. Build the trading bot:
   ```bash
   cargo build --release
   ```

2. Run the setup script:
   ```bash
   sudo ./scripts/setup.sh
   ```

The setup script will:
- Create a dedicated system user and group
- Create necessary directories
- Install the binary
- Install configuration files
- Set up the systemd service
- Start the trading bot

Directory Structure
-----------------
- Binary: /usr/local/bin/trading-bot
- Configuration: /var/lib/trading-bot/config/
- Data: /var/lib/trading-bot/data/
- Backups: /var/lib/trading-bot/backups/

Service Management
----------------
- Start service: `sudo systemctl start trading-bot`
- Stop service: `sudo systemctl stop trading-bot`
- Restart service: `sudo systemctl restart trading-bot`
- Check status: `sudo systemctl status trading-bot`
- View logs: `sudo journalctl -u trading-bot`

Troubleshooting
--------------
If the service fails to start:
1. Check the logs: `sudo journalctl -u trading-bot`
2. Verify file permissions
3. Check configuration file syntax
4. Ensure all dependencies are installed

Security Notes
-------------
- The trading bot runs as a dedicated system user
- Configuration files are readable only by the bot user
- Data directories are owned by the bot user
- Service runs with limited system privileges 